author: Guardian Staff
title: One More Time: WA Liberals groove to Daft Punk at 2017 campaign launch – video
text:
Western Australian politics One More Time: WA Liberals groove to Daft Punk at 2017 campaign launch – video 
Members of the Western Australian Liberal party got into the spirit of things at their election campaign launch on Sunday with French electronic duo Daft Punk’s 2001 hit One More Time. The government led by the Liberal premier, Colin Barnett, is seeking a third four-year term but have had to contend with poor polling and criticism from the National party and others over a preference deal with One Nation that may allow them to hang on to power View more sharing options
